<eesti>M&auml;nguasja turule laskmine </eesti>
<inglise>Placing of toys on market </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses m&otilde;istetakse m&auml;nguasja turule laskmise all m&auml;nguasja m&uuml;&uuml;mist v&otilde;i muul viisil tasuta v&otilde;i tasu eest &uuml;leandmist tootja v&otilde;i importija poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Regulation, placing of toys on the market means the sale of toys or the distribution thereof by the producer or importer in any other manner without charge or for a charge. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turule v&otilde;ib lasta ainult k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud ohutusn&otilde;uetele vastava m&auml;nguasja, mis: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A toy may be placed on the market only if it complies with the safety requirements provided for in this Regulation and: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on kavandatud ja valmistatud vastavalt m&auml;nguasja ohutust k&auml;sitlevatele Eesti standarditele v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) is designed and manufactured according to the Estonian standards concerning the safety of toys, or </inglise>
<eesti>2) on kavandatud ja valmistatud vastavalt protot&uuml;&uuml;bile, millele volitatud asutus on teostanud t&uuml;&uuml;bikatsetuse ning v&auml;ljastanud vastavussertifikaadi. </eesti>
<inglise>2) is designed and manufactured according to the model with regard to which an approved body has conducted type examination and issued a certificate of conformity. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;ike 2 punktis 1 nimetatud Eesti standarditena arvestatakse j&auml;rgmiseid standardeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The following standards are considered the Estonian standards specified in clause (2) 1): </inglise>
