<eesti>&Uuml;ldine ohutusn&otilde;ue </eesti>
<inglise>General safety requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(1) M&auml;nguasi ei tohi ohustada kasutajate v&otilde;i teiste isikute turvalisust v&otilde;i tervist selle kasutamisel sihip&auml;raselt v&otilde;i muul eeldataval m&otilde;istusp&auml;rasel viisil, arvestades laste tavap&auml;rast k&auml;itumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A toy shall not jeopardise the safety or health of users or third parties when it is used as intended or in any other foreseeable and reasonable way, bearing in mind the normal behaviour of children. </inglise>
<eesti>See n&otilde;ue kehtib ka siis, kui m&auml;nguasi on kavandatud ja valmistatud vastavalt &sect; 2 l&otilde;ikele 2. </eesti>
<inglise>This requirement also applies if a toy is designed and manufactured according to subsection 2 (2). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&auml;nguasi peab vastama k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud ohutusn&otilde;uetele m&auml;nguasja kogu etten&auml;htud ja normaalse kasutusaja kestel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A toy shall comply with the safety requirements provided for in this Regulation throughout the period of its foreseeable and normal use. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;nguasjaga seonduva v&otilde;imaliku ohu hindamine </eesti>
<inglise>Assessment of possible risks relating to toys </inglise>
<eesti>(1) M&auml;nguasja ohtlikkus v&otilde;ib olla seotud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The risks relating to a toy are those: </inglise>
<eesti>1) m&auml;nguasja disaini, konstruktsiooni v&otilde;i materjalidega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) which are connected with the design, construction or composition of the toy; </inglise>
<eesti>2) m&auml;nguasja kasutamisega, kusjuures m&auml;nguasja konstruktsiooni v&otilde;i koostisosade muutmisega ei ole v&otilde;imalik ohtu t&auml;ielikult k&otilde;rvaldada ilma, et teiseneks m&auml;nguasja otstarve v&otilde;i muutuksid tema peamised omadused. </eesti>
<inglise>2) which are inherent in the use of the toy and cannot be completely eliminated by modifying the construction and composition of the toy without altering its function or depriving it of its essential properties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) M&auml;nguasja kasutamisega seotud v&otilde;imaliku ohu hindamisel tuleb arvestada lapse v&otilde;imeid ja oskusi, samuti vajadusel lapse tegevust j&auml;lgiva t&auml;iskasvanu v&otilde;imalusi ohu v&auml;ltimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Assessment of the degree of risk present in the use of a toy shall take into account the abilities and skills of the child and, where appropriate, the opportunities which supervising adults have to prevent such risk. </inglise>
<eesti>Seejuures tuleb erilist t&auml;helepanu p&ouml;&ouml;rata m&auml;nguasjadele, mis oma otstarbe, m&otilde;&otilde;tmete ja muude omaduste poolest on m&otilde;eldud kasutamiseks alla 3-aastastele lastele. </eesti>
<inglise>This applies in particular to toys which, by virtue of their functions, dimensions and other characteristics, are intended for use by children of under 3 years of age. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud p&otilde;him&otilde;tte j&auml;rgimiseks tuleb vajaduse korral t&auml;psustada m&auml;nguasja kasutaja minimaalne vanus ja/v&otilde;i kas m&auml;nguasja kasutamisel on vajalik t&auml;iskasvanu j&auml;relevalve. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) To observe the principle specified in subsection (2), a minimum age for users of toys and/or the need to ensure that they are used only under adult supervision shall be specified where appropriate. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) M&auml;nguasjal v&otilde;i selle m&uuml;&uuml;gipakendil olev m&auml;rgistus, samuti m&auml;nguasja juurde kuuluvad kasutusjuhendid peavad juhtima lapse v&otilde;i tema j&auml;relevaataja t&auml;helepanu m&auml;nguasja kasutamisega kaasneda v&otilde;ivatele ohtudele ja nende v&auml;ltimise v&otilde;imalustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Labels on toys or their sales packaging, and the instructions for use which accompany toys shall draw the attention of children or their supervisors to the risks involved in using the toys and to the ways of avoiding such risks. </inglise>
